## Output Format (strict JSON)
Respond with **only** valid JSON (no markdown fences):
{
  "summary": "<2-4 sentences: how {{ user_name }} thinks and decides>",
  "thinking_style": "<how they reason — risk tolerance, priorities, blind spots to watch>",
  "likes": ["<approach or recommendation type they favor>", "..."],
  "dislikes": ["<approach or framing they reject>", "..."],
  "new_memory": {
    "title": "<short title for this learning>",
    "insight": "<one durable insight from this disagreement>",
    "likes": ["<specific preference revealed>"],
    "dislikes": ["<specific rejection revealed>"]
  }
}

Keep likes/dislikes lists to at most 12 items each (merge and dedupe). The new_memory will be appended to their memory log.
